Nazarine DC | Smart Energy Management SystemNazarine DC is a high-performance, full-stack IoT platform designed for real-time telemetry, historical data aggregation, and predictive insights. Engineered to bridge the gap between physical hardware (ESP32) and high-level data visualization, it provides a robust pipeline for smart home and industrial energy grids.🚀 Key AdvantagesHigh-Fidelity Telemetry: Achieves sub-second latency via WebSockets for instantaneous power, voltage, and current feedback.Hardware-in-the-Loop: Seamlessly interfaces with ESP32 microcontrollers using standardized JSON telemetry schemas.Intelligent Aggregation: Backend integration converts raw power (kW) into accumulated energy (kWh), real-time costs (₦), and carbon metrics (kg CO2).AI-Ready Architecture: Infrastructure is optimized for Pandas-ready data structures, supporting future machine learning deployment for grid forecasting.🛠️ Tech StackComponentTechnologyFrontendHTML5, Tailwind CSS, JavaScript (ES6+), Chart.jsBackendPython 3.x, FastAPI, Uvicorn (ASGI), WebSocketsDatabaseSQLite3 (Persistent Time-Series Storage)💻 Local Setup & Execution1. PrerequisitesEnsure you have Python 3.7+ installed.2. Install DependenciesBashpip install fastapi uvicorn pydantic
3. Initialize the DatabaseSeed your database with 24 hours of historical telemetry to populate the dashboard:Bashpython seed_db.py
Note: This generates a verdant_memory.db file in your directory.4. Launch the Backend ServerBashuvicorn main:app --reload
The server will be live at http://127.0.0.1:8000.5. Open the DashboardOpen energy_dashboard.html directly in your browser.Pro-Tip: Avoid VS Code "Live Server" extensions to prevent infinite refresh loops caused by frequent database updates. Opening the file via file:/// is recommended.6. Simulated Hardware TestingIf no physical ESP32 is connected:Open the Browser Console (F12).Paste the JavaScript Simulator script provided in the documentation.Hit Enter to begin streaming live telemetry to the server.Developed as a professional mechatronics and aerospace-grade energy monitoring solution.